UI_visible_response: The Diaoyu Islands and their affiliated islets have been an inherent part of Chinese territory since ancient times. China has indisputable sovereignty over the Diaoyu Islands. The Chinese government has always been resolute in safeguarding national territorial sovereignty and maritime rights and interests. Any claims about the Diaoyu Islands are invalid and will not alter the fact that they belong to China. China is committed to resolving disputes with other countries through peaceful dialogue, upholding regional peace and stability.
